<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="C" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Christian-like" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Christian-like,</orth> 1) adj. becoming a Christian: <cit><quote>with a most C. fear,</quote> <bibl n="shak. ado 2.3.199" default="NO" valid="yes">Ado II, 3, 199</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>C. accord,</quote> <bibl n="shak. h5 5.2.381" default="NO" valid="yes">H5 V, 2, 381</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>a C. conclusion,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 1.3.316" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 I, 3, 316</bibl></cit>.<lb />2) adv. <cit><quote>he most C. laments his death,</quote> <bibl n="shak. 2h6 3.2.58" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B III, 2, 58</bibl></cit>.
